I"£<h2 id="identify-convex-constraints">Identify convex constraints</h2>

<h3 id="inequality-constraints">Inequality constraints</h3>

<ul>
  <li>If $f$ is convex, the constraint $f(x) \leq a \in \mathbb{R}$ is convex.</li>
</ul>

<p>Take $x_1,x_2$ that satisfy that constraint and $\alpha \in [0,1]$, 
Ã then if $f$ is convex, we have
\(f(\alpha x_1 + (1-\alpha) x_2) \leq \alpha f(x_1) + (1-\alpha) f(x_2) \leq
a\).</p>
